# Implementation Plan — ExceptionIQ v3 MVP Build

Build a fully functional ExceptionIQ application using the modular monolith setup (Django + React + FastAPI + Postgres). The focus is on functionality and making the MVP highly interactive and testable. Notifications are scraped for now.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **Database Auto-Seeding**: A custom seed script (`seed_db`) will run on startup in `docker-compose.yml`. It sets up a default entity (`Acme Corporation`), users for each role (`admin`, `analyst`, `approver`, `manager` - all with password same as username), and standard routing rules.
> - **User Switcher**: To easily test role-based views and the **Maker-Checker** resolution flow without tedious login/logout steps, we will implement a User Switcher dropdown in the top navbar.
> - **Local AI Fallback**: If `GROQ_API_KEY` is not provided in `.env`, the FastAPI AI service will use a smart rule-based exception analyzer to construct high-fidelity exception summaries, preventing empty panels.

